 In a short statement released on Wednesday, Zuma wished the star a speedy recovery."President Jacob Zuma has wished South African gospel music star, Mr Lundi Tyamara, a speedy recovery," the statement reads."Mr Tyamara, one of South Africa's talented gospel artists and a multi-award recipient, has been hospitalised since December last year. President Zuma has urged South Africans to keep Mr Tyamara and his family in their thoughts and prayers."Tyamara was admitted a month ago at Edenvale Hospital for stomach TB and a liver condition.News broke yesterday that Tyamara was been transferred to Intensive Care Unit (ICU).